魯羅","lifeSummary":"当Lady Margaret Cornwall Kayle于1385年出生在英国英格兰可瓦爾特魯羅时，她的父亲METCALFE KAYLE20岁，母亲MARGARET DE CLARE20岁。她于1404年与John Lucombe III在英国可瓦爾特魯羅结婚。他们至少是3个女儿的父母。她去世于1445年在英国英格兰戴文斯迪文斯同享年60岁。"},"hr":{"1385–1445":"1385.–1445.","1384–1410":"1384–1410.","1384–1435":"1384–1435.","1403–Female":"1403–preminula","1405–1493":"1405.–1493","1420–Female":"1420.–preminula","1435–1493":"1435.–1493","1365–1385":"1365–1385.","AFT 1435":"nakon 1435.","1385":"1385.","1384":"1384","1493":"1493","1404":"1404.","1403":"1403","1435":"1435.","1445":"1445.","1410":"1410.","1420":"1420.","1365":"1365","about 1403":"oko 1403.","1405":"1405.","Stevenstone, Devon, England":"Stevenstone, Devon, Engleska, United Kingdom","Cornwall Co., Eng.":"Cornwall, England","Eastwell, Kent, England":"Eastwell, Kent, England","Truro, Cornwall, England":"Truro, Cornwall, England"},"cs":{"1385–1445":"1385–1445","1384–1410":"1384–1410","1384–1435":"1384–1435","1403–Female":"1403–Zesnulá","1405–1493":"1405–1493","1420–Female":"1420–Zesnulá","1435–1493":"1435–1493","1365–1385":"1365–1385","AFT 1435":"po 1435","1385":"1385","1384":"1384","1493":"1493","1404":"1404","1403":"1403","1435":"1435","1445":"1445","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1365":"1365","about 1403":"okolo 1403","1405":"1405","Stevenstone, Devon, England":"Stevenstone, Devon, Anglie, United Kingdom","Cornwall Co., Eng.":"Cornwall, Anglie","Eastwell, Kent, England":"Eastwell, Kent, Anglie","Truro, Cornwall, England":"Truro, Cornwall, Anglie"},"da":{"1385–1445":"1385–1445","1384–1410":"1384–1410","1384–1435":"1384–1435","1403–Female":"1403–Afdød","1405–1493":"1405–1493","1420–Female":"1420–Afdød","1435–1493":"1435–1493","1365–1385":"1365–1385","AFT 1435":"efter 1435","1385":"1385","1384":"1384","1493":"1493","1404":"1404","1403":"1403","1435":"1435","1445":"1445","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1365":"1365","about 1403":"omkring 1403","1405":"1405","Stevenstone, Devon, England":"Stevenstone, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Cornwall Co., Eng.":"Cornwall, England","Eastwell, Kent, England":"Eastwell, Kent, England","Truro, Cornwall, England":"Truro, Cornwall, England"},"nl":{"1385–1445":"1385–1445","1384–1410":"1384–1410","1384–1435":"1384–1435","1403–Female":"1403–Overleden","1405–1493":"1405–1493","1420–Female":"1420–Overleden","1435–1493":"1435–1493","1365–1385":"1365–1385","AFT 1435":"na 1435","1385":"1385","1384":"1384","1493":"1493","1404":"1404","1403":"1403","1435":"1435","1445":"1445","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1365":"1365","about 1403":"circa 1403","1405":"1405","Stevenstone, Devon, England":"Stevenstone, Devon, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Cornwall Co., Eng.":"Cornwall, England","Eastwell, Kent, England":"Eastwell, Kent, England","Truro, Cornwall, England":"Truro, Cornwall, England"},"en":{"1385–1445":"1385–1445","1384–1410":"1384–1410","1384–1435":"1384–1435","1403–Female":"1403–Deceased","1405–1493":"1405–1493","1420–Female":"1420–Deceased","1435–1493":"1435–1493","1365–1385":"1365–1385","AFT 1435":"after 1435","1385":"1385","1384":"1384","1493":"1493","1404":"1404","1403":"1403","1435":"1435","1445":"1445","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1365":"1365","about 1403":"about 1403","1405":"1405","Stevenstone, Devon, England":"Stevenstone, Devon, England, United Kingdom","Cornwall Co., Eng.":"Cornwall, England","Eastwell, Kent, England":"Eastwell, Kent, England","Truro, Cornwall, England":"Truro, Cornwall, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kayle","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Kabel   or of some other similar (like-sounding) surname (compare   Cable  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Kabel","meanings":["German: topographic name from Middle Low German <i>kabel</i> ‘lot field’. This alludes to the custom in North Rhine-Westphalia of alloting communally owned plots of land to individual farmers by the drawing of lots.","Dutch: metonymic occupational name for someone who produced cables, from Dutch <i>kabel</i> ‘cable’, or a topographic or habitational name referring to a house which was distinguished by the image of a cable, possibly because it referred to a manufactory of ropes and cables."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]},{"name":"Cornwall","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Irish: Corn, a goblet, a drinking cup, a tumbler, so called because in ancient times drinking cups were commonly made of horn (corn), and aill, a cliff, meaning the horny cliff"],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Margaret Cornwall Kayle was born in 1385, in Truro, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom, her father, METCALFE KAYLE, was 20 and her mother, MARGARET DE CLARE, was 20. She married John Lucombe III in 1404, in Truro, Cornwall, England. They were the parents of at least 3 daughters. She died in 1445, in Stevenstone, Devon, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1385–1445":"1385–1445","1384–1410":"1384–1410","1384–1435":"1384–1435","1403–Female":"1403–Surnud","1405–1493":"1405–1493","1420–Female":"1420–Surnud","1435–1493":"1435–1493","1365–1385":"1365–1385","AFT 1435":"pärast 1435","1385":"1385","1384":"1384","1493":"1493","1404":"1404","1403":"1403","1435":"1435","1445":"1445","1410":"1410","1420":"1420","1365":"1365","about 1403":"umbes 1403","1405":"1405","Stevenstone, Devon, England":"Stevenstone, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cornwall Co., Eng.":"Cornwall, England","Eastwell, Kent, England":"Eastwell, Kent, England","Truro, Cornwall, England":"Truro, Cornwall, England"},"fi":{"1385–1445":"1385–1445","1384–1410":"1384–1410","1384–1435":"1384–1435","1403–Female":"1403–Kuollut","1405–1493":"1405–1493","1420–Female":"1420–Kuollut","1435–1493":"1435–1493","1365–1385":"1365–1385","AFT 1435":"1435 jälkeen